## 4. EVM local payment lacks live Alchemy regression coverage

Status: confirmed
Severity: medium

The built-in `evm-local` payment path is covered by Rust unit tests for amount
calculation and by compile-time checks, but it has not been verified against a
real Alchemy API key and real ERC20 transfers. The implementation now uses
Alchemy JSON-RPC `eth_getLogs`; production verification still needs at least one
real BNB Smart Chain USDT/USDC payment and one mismatch/expired-payment case.
It also needs a same-amount multi-address concurrency check, an overpay-tolerance
check when enabled, and a manual `tx_hash` confirmation check. Alchemy free-tier
limits vary by chain and method, so `log_scan_block_range` and watcher frequency
should be checked against the active Alchemy plan before production use.

References:

- `src/services/evm_local_service.rs`
- `migrations/0012_evm_local_payments.sql`
- `docs/README.md`: EVM 本地收款

